## Component Philosophy

**Use primitives for layout, components for repeated elements:**
- ✅ Main content containers: `View` (not Card)
- ✅ Form inputs: Custom wrappers around Paper primitives
- ✅ Platform-specific: Use `.Android`/`.IOS` variants when needed
- ✅ Manual build when library fails: Don't fight the library

**Global styling:**
- All components support global style changes
- Modify component file → affects entire app
- Designer-friendly: Single file changes cascade everywhere

---

## Notes & Considerations

### Data Privacy
- All data stored locally in AsyncStorage.
- No server communication in current version (JSON Server for dev only).
- User data never leaves the device.
- Offline-first by design.

### Asset Types
- Migrated from web prototype: property, bank-accounts, investment, pensions, life-insurance, private-company-shares, assets-held-through-business, agricultural-assets, crypto-currency, important-items.
- When adding new types, ensure consistency with web prototype.

### Navigation Flow
- Expo Router file-based navigation.
- Categories can be selected/deselected in bequeathal flow.
- Navigation uses router.push/back/replace.

### Styling
- React Native Paper for base components.
- Kindling brand colors in `src/styles/theme.ts`.
- StyleSheet for all component styling.
- No inline styles - use StyleSheet.create().

